HEADWORD: budgie
<hw>budg"ie</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>small Australian parakeet
(<spn>Melopsittacus undulatus</spn>) usually light green with black and
yellow markings in the wild but bred in many colors.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> budgerigar, budgereegah, budgerygah, grass parakeet,
lovebird, shell parakeet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

